Let's be clear: while it is easy to discuss, this is 
\f1\i not
\f0\i0  an inherently straightforward task for a product team (even a one-person team) to execute on. In my experience, I've found it can be beneficial to start by dissecting your interface into its hierarchical data components. Put simply, this means you should break down a given screen into an 
\f1\i ordered list
\f0\i0  of information on the page. As with many design-related activities, this is firmly rooted in science. 
